Kim Jong Il inspects KPA unit no. 1200 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 2 (KCNA) - General Secretary Kim Jong Il inspected KPA unit no. 1200 on Friday.
 Upon arriving in the unit on the front, he learned about the performance of the unit's duty. Then he walked up an observation post to see soldiers in training.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was greatly satisfied to see all the soldiers of the unit fully prepared to be one-match-for-a-hundred fighters capable of defeating any formidable enemy at a single blow and firmly protecting the security of the country and people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set forth highly important tasks to be fulfilled to increase the combat capability of the unit in every way. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said the valiant soldiers of the people's army single-heartedly rallied around the party are standing guard over the forefront where a grim class struggle is under way, demonstrating the heroic stamina of socialist Korea by weathering out the raging wind raised by imperialists with a violent revolutionary storm, adding that no force on earth can overpower these great forces firmly determined not to allow any aggressors to dare invade the inviolable territory of our country but wipe them out to the last one at the risk of their lives. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He took warm care of the living of the soldiers with paternal love, looking round entertainment and logistic facilities of the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He met with commanding officers of a company under the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that it is of weighty importance in increasing the combat capability of the whole army to strengthen the company, a main combat unit and a cell of the people's army, he set forth specific tasks to do so. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Much pleased to learn that the unit has built all the logistic facilities needed for the living of the soldiers and created good dietary conditions by meticulously organizing the supply service, he highly praised its successes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He spared time to see an art performance given by soldiers of  the company under the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He gave them a pair of binoculars, a machine- gun and an automatic rifle as gifts and had a photograph taken with them.

KCNA slams Ri Hoe Chang's sycophancy
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 2 (KCNA) -- Ri Hoe Chang, president of the "Grand National Party" in South Korea, during his U.S. junket, did not bother to let loose a whole string of jargons intended to disturb the peace and stability on the Korean peninsula and perpetuate the division of the nation, stoking up the fellow countrymen's anger.
 Adamantly opposed to the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration and supporting the U.S. hostile policy toward the DPRK, he talked about the "verification" of the north and slandered even the inter-Korean cooperation including Mt. Kumgang tourism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is an anti-reunification, sycophantic and treacherous act intended to seize power and seek personal comfort, indifferent to the destiny of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His true colors as a national separatist were laid bare through the political background against which his U.S. trip took place and its aims. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. hardline conservatives who seem to be upbeat with the "war against terrorism" as a momentum are increasing pressure on the sovereign states advocating independence. Ri flew into Washington to meet his masters with Bush's visit to South Korea at hand. He begged them to keep the U.S. forces in South Korea permanently, clamoring about the "verification" of the north and "reduction of its conventional armed forces". This fully revealed his unlimited greed for power as a colonial puppet.   He is keen to seize power in the next presidential election with the backing of the U.S. hardline conservatives. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He is a top-class traitor who allows himself to serve as a running dog for foreign forces in a bid to satisfy his greed for power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If such a guy, who seeks permanent division and confrontation, not reconciliation and unity between the north and the south, comes to power, it will spark only a fratricidal war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is more intolerable is that Ri, inhuman political prostitute bereft of any elementary ability to judge the interests and aspiration of the nation and the trend of the times, was doggedly opposed to the joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The joint declaration is a landmark of reunification which the north and the south confirmed before the world and history. Opposing it is little short of totally denying the existence of the nation itself. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will not sit with him unless he makes an apology for his crimes.

KCNA on Bush's belligerent remarks
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 2 (KCNA) -- U.S. President Bush in a "state of the union address" before the congress on Jan. 30 cited the DPRK and some other nations as "an axis of evil" and "states threatening the world peace." And he blustered that the U.S. will not permit them to do so and operations should be carried on as planned.
 This reveals the U.S. reckless intention to seize the DPRK by force of arms after designating it as the second target of "anti-terrorism war." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His outburst is little short of a declaration of war against the DPRK, and this may once again bring the military situation on the Korean peninsula to the brink of war.
 More than once the DPRK has declared that it has nothing to do with terrorism, and it has posed no threat to any country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nevertheless, Bush expressed an intention to stifle the DPRK by force of arms, undisguisedly pointing a finger at it this time. This can never be overlooked nor allowed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His remarks clearly show that the U.S.-proposed "resumption of dialogue" with the DPRK is intended not for the improvement of the bilateral relations but for the realization of the U.S. aggressive military strategy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the steadfast stand and transparent will to counter force with force and confrontation with confrontation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should not misjudge the inexhaustible military strength of the DPRK. It has fully equipped itself with powerful offensive and defensive means, tightening its belt over the past years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK is fully capable of fighting a war with the U.S. it should clearly know that the option to "strike" is not its monopoly. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. ignites a war of aggression at last, the army and people of the DPRK will mercilessly wipe out the aggressors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We are sharply watching the ill-boding moves of the U.S., in full readiness.

Greetings to foreign state leaders
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 2 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il, General Secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea, Chairman of the National Defence Commission of the DPRK and Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army, sent messages of greetings to state leaders of different countries on the New Year Juche 91 (2002).
 Among them are Jaber al-Ahmed al-Jaber al-Sabah, Amir of Kuwait, Bhumibol Adulyadej, King of Thailand, Lansana Conte, President of Guinea, Olusegun Obasanjo, President and commander-in-chief of the armed forces of Nigeria, Moammer El Gaddafi, leader of the Great September First Revolution of Libya, Paul Kagame, President of Rwanda, Mohamed the Sixth, King of Morocco, Omar Hassan Ahmed al-Bashir, President of Sudan, Abdoulaye Wade, President of Senegal, France Albert Rene, President of Seychelles, Obiang Nguema Mbasogo, President and head of state of Equatorial Guinea and Founder-Chairman of the Democratic Party of Equatorial Guinea, Ismail Omar Guelleh, President of Djibouti, Denis Sassou Nguesso, President of Congo, Joseph Kabila, President of the Democratic Republic of Congo, and Mohamed Hosni Mubarak, President of Egypt. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Extending warm greetings to them on the New Year Juche 91 (2002), Kim Jong Il expressed belief that the friendly and cooperative relations between the DPRK and those countries would further develop and wished them success in their work for the prosperity of their countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He sent a message of greetings to Jacques Diouf, director-general of the Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations.

Bush's projected trip to S. Korea protested
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 2 (KCNA) -- The Association for Peace and Reunification (Phyongthongsa) reportedly held a rally on January 29 in protest against Bush's projected trip to South Korea.
 Co-representative So Kyong Won at the rally recalled that the unjust introduction of 100 f-15k fighters worth 10 billion dollars imposed by the U.S. upon South Korea is under discussion by media, and voiced opposition to Bush's scheduled junket aimed to sell them to South Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A statement adopted at the rally said that they resolutely oppose the visit to South Korea by Bush, a stumbling block in the way of achieving national reunification and protecting people's right to existence, check the forced purchase of weapons and call to task the crimes of the flunkeyist ministry of national defense against the nation and the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prior to the rally the joint council of organizations against Bush's visit to South Korea also held a meeting on Jan. 24 to work out a concrete plan to protest Bush's trip to South Korea.

Juche idea study group formed in Kirgyzstan
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 2 (KCNA) -- A Juche idea study group was inaugurated with due ceremony in Kirgyzstan on the occasion of the birthday of leader Kim Jong Il.
 At the ceremony held in Bishkek on Jan. 28 the director of the "Stroimekhanizatsiya" co., ltd in a report said that it is their mission to follow the Juche idea and embody it in conformity with the actual conditions of Kirgyzstan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has steadily developed in depth the Juche idea fathered by President Kim Il Sung, thus glorifying people-centered socialism, he said, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people have adopted the Juche idea-based line of independence in politics, self-supporting in economy and self-reliance in national defence as a basic principle of the revolution and construction and implemented it, thereby firmly defending socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The first secretary of the central committee of the Communist Party of Kirgyzstan made a congratulatory address at the ceremony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The director was elected chief of the group. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A letter to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the ceremony.

Rodong Sinmun comments on U.S. mass killings
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 2 (KCNA) -- BBC recently confirmed the fact that the U.S. imperialist aggressors indiscriminately killed civilians during the Korean War.
 Commenting on it, Rodong Sinmun today says this has made clearer the truth about the massacres committed by the GIs in Rogun-ri and other parts of Korea during the war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists are, however, seeking to evade a probe into the truth about the cases and shirk their responsibility for them, the commentary notes, and says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This reveals the arrogance and shamelessness of the U.S. imperialist aggressors who have engaged themselves in high-handed practices in South Korea. Such attitude is an intolerable mockery of the Korean nation as it indicates their intention to continue killing Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our fellow countrymen can never pardon the u.s. imperialist murderers. If those aggressors are allowed to stay in South Korea our fellow countrymen will have to shed more blood and the entire nation will face a nuclear calamity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is impossible to co-exist with the aggressors even a moment. An eye for an eye, and a tooth for a tooth.

11th Paektusan Cup international figure-skating festival to be held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 2 (KCNA) -- The 11th Paektusan Cup international figure-skating festival is to be held in Pyongyang on the occasion of the auspicious February holiday.
 The festival will be all the more significant and unique because it is held by the unanimous aspiration and desire of all people to celebrate the birthday of leader Kim Jong Il, a peerlessly great man for the century and the great sun of the 21st century, as the most significant holiday common to humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The festival will include domestic games and exhibition performances of foreign and domestic merited figure skaters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 11th Paektusan Cup international figure-skating festival will be held amid the great expectation and concern of the Korean people and the world progressives and athletes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It will more significantly adorn the February holiday with fresh pictures and colors.

U.S. anti-DPRK smear campaign blasted 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 2 (KCNA) -- Some U.S. figures affected with nuclear hysteria are busy spreading rumors that the DPRK might "possess one or two nuclear bombs" and that it is playing a certain "trick". Not content with this, they are bringing the DPRK's "nuclear issue" even to an international disarmament conference.
 In this regard Minju Joson today says in a signed commentary: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 While floating the fiction of "North Korea's suspected nuclear development," they claim the story is based on "information provided by the U.S. CIA" in a bid to make it plausible. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This clearly indicates how desperately they are working to charge the DPRK with "nuclear proliferation". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has sincerely implemented its commitment under the DPRK-U.S. agreed framework, even suffering enormous loss of electricity due to the freeze of its independent nuclear power industry. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The United States, however, has not honestly implemented its commitments under the framework though seven years have passed since it was published. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In clamouring about the "nuclear issue" of the DPRK the U.S. seeks a sinister aim.     It is aimed at pushing forward its program to beef up its nuclear armed force under the pretext of stopping the "nuclear program" in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The United States should eliminate weapons of mass destruction and drop its bad habit of pointing an accusing finger at others instead of feeling guilty.

Kimjongilia grows in different countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 2 (KCNA) -- Immortal Kimjongilia is in full bloom in different countries.
 According to data available, Kimjongilia, a flower of the sun, has been raised and brought into bloom by the progressives in more than 80 countries and regions, captivated by the idea, leadership and virtues of leader Kim Jong Il since its appearance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kimjongilia was produced first on the occasion of his birthday, auspicious February 16, Juche 77 (1988). It has been raised in Korea and other countries, disseminated by the Central Botanical Garden in Pyongyang according to the unanimous aspirations and desire of the Korean people as well as the world people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kimjongilia greenhouses have opened in Yanji, Dandong and Shanghai of China, Madagascar, Ethiopia, etc. The Nordic Association of Kimjongilia was organized in Stockholm by flower lovers and experts of Sweden, Finland, Norway and Denmark, the Kimjongilia Association in Mongolia and the Kimjongilia lovers' societies in Japan.

Posters for 6th Kimjongilia Show produced
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 2 (KCNA) -- Posters for the 6th Kimjongilia Show to be held on the occasion of the auspicious February holiday, the birthday of Kim Jong Il, were produced.
 Inscribed on the posters are a slogan "Long live general Kim Jong Il, sun of the 21st century" which reflects infinite veneration and praise of the Korean people and humankind and the aspirations and desire of the times and letters "celebration-February 16" and "the 6th Kimjongilia Show." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among them are a poster with a picture of Kimjongilia against the background of firecrackers in the sky above Jong Il Peak and a poster with a picture of Kimjongilia, flower of the sun, against the background of Lake Chon on Mt. Paektu glowing with sunrays. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is written in the posters that the show will be held at the Grand People's Study House from February 13 to 20, Juche 91 (2002).
